# Spinor.Weyl

Weyl (chiral) spinors.

A Weyl spinor is a 2-component complex spinor transforming under one of the two
irreducible representations of SL(2,ℂ):
  - Left-Weyl  (1/2, 0): transforms as ψ ↦ M ψ
  - Right-Weyl (0, 1/2): transforms as χ̄ ↦ M̄ χ̄  (complex conjugate representation)

Status: stub.
